<taxonomicName authorityName="Aube" authorityYear="1838" box="[140,299,1152,1179]" class="Insecta" family="Gyrinidae" genus="Gyrinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis box="[140,299,1152,1179]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">Gyrinus affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded from 
<collectingRegion box="[524,705,1152,1179]" country="Canada" name="New Brunswick" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">New Brunswick</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Oygur S &amp; Wolfe GW" box="[748,1035,1152,1178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="361" pagination="1 - 97" refId="ref7625" refString="Oygur S, Wolfe GW (1991) Classification, distribution and phylogeny of North American (north of Mexico) species of Gyrinus Muller (Coleoptera: Gyrinidae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 207: 1 - 97." type="journal article" year="1991">Oygur and Wolfe (1991)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<collectingRegion country="Canada" name="Nova Scotia" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">Nova Scotia</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Oygur S &amp; Wolfe GW" box="[254,542,1187,1214]" pageId="6" pageNumber="361" pagination="1 - 97" refId="ref7625" refString="Oygur S, Wolfe GW (1991) Classification, distribution and phylogeny of North American (north of Mexico) species of Gyrinus Muller (Coleoptera: Gyrinidae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 207: 1 - 97." type="journal article" year="1991">Oygur and Wolfe (1991)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Roughley RE" box="[601,798,1187,1214]" pageId="6" pageNumber="361" pagination="72 - 673" refId="ref7727" refString="Roughley RE (1991) Family Gyrinidae: Whirligig Beetles. In: Bousquet Y (Ed) Checklist of Beetles of Canada and Alaska. Ottawa, Ontario: Agriculture Canada, publication 1861 / E: pp. 72 - 673. http: // www. canacoll. org / Coleo / Checklist / PDF files / GYRINIDAE. pdf [accessed 29 June 2009]" type="journal article" year="1991">Roughley (1991)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[863,1107,1187,1213]" country="Canada" name="Prince Edward Island" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">Prince Edward Island</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Majka CG" box="[175,335,1223,1249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="361" pagination="239 - 260" refId="ref7452" refString="Majka CG (2008) The aquatic Coleoptera of Prince Edward Island, Canada: new records and faunal composition. In: Majka CG, Klimaszewski J (Eds) Biodiversity, Biosystematics, and Ecology of Canadian Coleoptera. ZooKeys 2: 239 - 260. http: // pensoftonline. net / zookeys / index. php / journal / article / viewFile / 25 / 37 [accessed 29 June 2009]" type="journal article" year="2008">Majka (2008)</bibRefCitation>
. It is one of the most abundant and widely distributed species in the region (Fig. 8). 
<bibRefCitation author="Oygur S &amp; Wolfe GW" box="[319,605,1258,1284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="361" pagination="1 - 97" refId="ref7625" refString="Oygur S, Wolfe GW (1991) Classification, distribution and phylogeny of North American (north of Mexico) species of Gyrinus Muller (Coleoptera: Gyrinidae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 207: 1 - 97." type="journal article" year="1991">Oygur and Wolfe (1991)</bibRefCitation>
recorded the species from streams and lakes while 
<bibRefCitation author="Morrissette R" box="[212,427,1293,1319]" pageId="6" pageNumber="361" pagination="1 - 43" refId="ref7605" refString="Morrissette R (1979) Les coleopteres Gyrinidae du Quebec. Cordulia, Supplement 8: 1 - 43." type="journal article" year="1979">Morrissette (1979)</bibRefCitation>
reported it from stagnant water. It is found in both lotic (41%) and lentic (59%) habitats (
<bibRefCitation author="Oygur S &amp; Wolfe GW" box="[523,793,1328,1354]" pageId="6" pageNumber="361" pagination="1 - 97" refId="ref7625" refString="Oygur S, Wolfe GW (1991) Classification, distribution and phylogeny of North American (north of Mexico) species of Gyrinus Muller (Coleoptera: Gyrinidae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 207: 1 - 97." type="journal article" year="1991">Oygur and Wolfe 1991</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
